b'Jennifer Castillo, Program Design Manager at US Foods and US Navy veteran, shares what her service means to her and how it helped prepare her for her career as a civilian:

\xe2\x80\x9cI consider being a Navy Veteran my greatest accomplishment outside of becoming a mom. I raised my right hand and swore to serve my country, up to, and including, laying down my life so that my fellow citizens can sleep safe at night. There is no greater honor. I served as a Mass Communications Specialist in the US Navy - the skills and experience I gained during my military service is the whole reason I have the career I do today in communications. At US Foods, I manage large internal communications, sales meetings, and direct national webinars/trainings. When the pandemic hit, it was like all my military training really came to life. I was calm in the chaos. I was a strategic thinker, a leader and able to adapt to the ever-changing environment in our business.\xe2\x80\x9d

We want to extend our thanks to Jennifer, and all of our veterans, Guards, and Reservists today, and every day, for their service to this country. We\xe2\x80\x99re honored to call you colleagues, friends, and family! #VeteransDay #ThankYouVeterans'
